# Zoom Security

Never expose the following in committed code or client-side examples:
- SDK secrets
- OAuth client secrets
- Server-to-Server OAuth credentials
- raw bearer tokens

## Preferred patterns

- Generate Meeting SDK or Video SDK signatures server-side
- Exchange OAuth credentials server-side
- Keep Zoom Docs, MCP, and REST API access tokens outside committed files
- Use `.env.example` for placeholders only

## Docs guidance

- If an example requires a secret, show the environment variable name, not a real value
- If a browser app needs authenticated data, document the backend handoff explicitly
